s:2098:"<h2>What is this?</h2>
<p>All Zen Grid Framework v4 themes have the ability to render the main menu as a one page menu that allows the user to smooth scroll to the specific row of modules on the page.</p>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/one-page/one-page-menu.jpg" alt="Meet the team" /></p>
<h2>Steps to recreate this module</h2>
<p><strong> Module Manager </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Navigate to the module manager in your Joomla administrator via extensions &gt; Module Manager</li>
<li>Click new</li>
<li>Select the zentools2 type module</li>
<li>Give the module a name that you will remember eg Meet the team</li>
<li>Assign the module to a module position (grid21).</li>
<li>Ensure the module is published</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/meet-the-team-module-settings.png" alt="Module settings" /></p>
<p><strong> Options </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Select the backstretch slideshow layout</li>
<li>Select your content source eg Joomla </li>
<li>Set your layout tags eg image, title, introtext, readmore</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/meet-the-team-layout.png" alt="Layout settings" /></p>
<p>Image settings.
<img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/image.png" alt="Image settings" />
Title Settings
<img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/title.png" alt="title settings" />
Introtext Settings
<img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/introtext.png" alt="title settings" />
Readmore Settings
<img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/readmore.png" alt="title settings" /></p>
<ol>
<li>Set your desired module settings eg slide duration etc</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/meet-the-team-options.png" alt="Module Options" /></p>
<p><strong> Content </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Go to the content panel</li>
<li>Adjust the content settings so that the module shows the correct content</li>
</ol>
<p><img src="/docs/ascent2/images/meet-the-team/meet-the-team-content.png" alt="Module Content" /></p>
<p><strong> Save the module </strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Click the save button in the top left of the page.</li>
</ol>";